00:46:21.990 --> 00:46:25.760
Let me refer to Abraham
Lincoln [laughter].

00:46:25.760 --> 00:46:32.310 position:56%
In that speech at Springfield Lyceum
in 1828 called on the perpetration

00:46:32.310 --> 00:46:36.390
of our political institutions,
in which Lincoln warns

00:46:36.390 --> 00:46:40.220
of our own self destruction
from within.

00:46:40.220 --> 00:46:44.030
He says, there is a
flaw in our system.

00:46:44.030 --> 00:46:47.420
And this is what Lincoln says.

00:46:47.420 --> 00:46:51.050
He says, there may be a
man who emerges seeking --

00:46:51.050 --> 00:46:53.750
and these are Lincoln's
words, not mine --

00:46:53.750 --> 00:47:03.270
celebrity and fame and distinction
beyond what is normal in politics.

00:47:03.270 --> 00:47:07.980
And he may seek to trample
down what exists in order

00:47:07.980 --> 00:47:13.120
to achieve distinction for himself.

00:47:13.120 --> 00:47:18.210
When that happens, said Lincoln,
the people must unite together

00:47:18.210 --> 00:47:20.800
and then Lincoln's words --

00:47:20.800 --> 00:47:26.930
act intelligently in
order to oppose him.

00:47:26.930 --> 00:47:30.080
Now Lincoln may have had
in mind Stephen A. Douglas,

00:47:30.080 --> 00:47:31.380
